\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls17\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls17\adjustright {Corporate Information Technology infrastructure -- OS, Security & directory services, object management services, etc. -- see diagram
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls17\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls17\adjustright {Enterprise document framework -- This shows how DM fits into a corporate Information Technology infrastructure
\par }\pard\plain \s2\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\outlinelevel1\adjustright \b\i\f1\cgrid {Evolution of Document Management Systems -- Jean
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard\plain \fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls18\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls18\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {In the beginning:  single-vendor proprietary client/server products, with proprietary solutions for integrating mass market applications to DM servers.
\par }\pard \qc\li360\sb120\sa120\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright {[Diagram:  single client/server pair]
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls18\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls18\adjustright {With Internet explosion:  single-vendor proprietary web server interfaces to DM servers.
\par }\pard \qc\li360\sb120\sa120\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright {[Diagram:  single proprietary web server working with a single vendor's repository]
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls18\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls18\adjustright {"Islands of information":  Over time, larger enterprises ended up with multiple incompatible clients, repositories, and web servers in various departmental systems, motivating the need for interoperability standards.
\par }\pard \qc\li360\sb120\sa120\widctlpar\adjustright {[Diagram:  Simple client/server diagram with multiple isolated client/server pairs]
\par [Diagram:  multiple proprietary web servers, each working with a single vendor's repository.]
\par [Diagram:  repository in middle picture, but with multiple repositories, to show the surge in interfaces to the repository, all in need of standardization.]
\par }\pard\plain \s2\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\outlinelevel1\adjustright \b\i\f1\cgrid {Document Management Standards Initiatives -- Chuck
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard\plain \fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls19\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls19\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Reference model for document management:  Document-Related Applications, Middleware/API, Repository Services
\par }\pard \qc\li360\sb120\sa120\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright {[Diagram:  front DM plane from DM reference model; following diagrams are based on this one]
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls19\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls19\adjustright {ODMA -- standardizing the integration of popular office applications with a particular vendor's DM system for storage and retrieval of documents, properties, etc.  Focus on 1.0 but mention 1.5, 2.0, Internet, and Workflow.
\par }\pard \qc\li360\sb120\sa120\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright {[Diagram: various ODMA apps (word processors, etc.) + proprietary ODMA provider + proprietary repository]
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls19\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls19\adjustright {DMA -- enabling a single client application to use a standard interface with DM systems from multiple vendors and search across all of them in a single query
\par }\pard \qc\li360\sb120\sa120\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright {[Diagram:  single client + middleware + multiple repositories]
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls19\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls19\adjustright {WebDAV -- standardizing the Internet protocol between authoring applications and web servers for overwrite protection, web page properties, collections of web pages, copy and move, versioning, and access control.
\par }\pard \qc\li360\sb120\sa120\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright {[Diagram:  word processor + web server with local DMS (use WebDAV flyer diagram?)]
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls19\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls19\adjustright {What each standard does well, what they don't try to do, and how they complement each other and work together.
\par }\pard \qc\li360\sb120\sa120\widctlpar\adjustright {[Diagram:  word processor + ODMA/DMA translator + DMA repositories]
\par [Diagram:  word processor + WebDAV web server + WebDAV/DMA translator + DMA repositories]
